 women’s nutritional needs during pregnancy and breastfeeding.","descriptionEn":"Blackmores Pregnancy & Breast-Feeding Gold Mini provides 20 important nutrients to support women’s nutritional needs during pregnancy and breastfeeding.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Pregnancy & Breast-Feeding Gold Mini Capsules All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Gold Mini Size Size 360 Capsules Blackmores Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Gold Mini provides 20 essential nutrients, including folic acid to help prevent neural tube defects and vitamin D3 to support maternal health during pregnancy and breastfeeding. Product Format Capsule Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Pregnancy Health Foetal Development No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Provides 500 micrograms of folic acid to support a healthy pregnancy and help prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida when taken at least four weeks before conception and during the first trimester. Contains 250 mg of omega-3 (DHA) to support healthy fetal brain development. Includes 1000 IU of vitamin D3 to support healthy fetal development. Provides a comprehensive range of nutrients to support the nutritional needs of women during pregnancy and breastfeeding. Dosage Adults Take 2 capsules two times a day, or as professionally prescribed. (Total: 4 capsules a day) Take with food. Warnings KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. Do not exceed the stated dose except on medical advice. lf you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. This product contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 micrograms for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. lf you are concerned about the health of yourself or your baby, talk to your health practitioner. If you have any pre-existing conditions, or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional.t. Contains sulfites, fish and soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings Provides 500 micrograms of folic acid to support a healthy pregnancy and help prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida when taken at least four weeks before conception and during the first trimester. Contains 250 mg of omega-3 (DHA) to support healthy fetal brain development. Includes 1000 IU of vitamin D3 to support healthy fetal development. Provides a comprehensive range of nutrients to support the nutritional needs of women during pregnancy and breastfeeding. Adults Take 2 capsules two times a day, or as professionally prescribed. (Total: 4 capsules a day) Take with food. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. Do not exceed the stated dose except on medical advice. lf you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. This product contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 micrograms for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. lf you are concerned about the health of yourself or your baby, talk to your health practitioner. If you have any pre-existing conditions, or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional.t. Contains sulfites, fish and soya bean products. Ingredients Active ingredients per capsule: Folic acid 125 micrograms Potassium iodide 49.3 micrograms equivalent iodine 37.5 micrograms Concentrated fish omega-3 triglycerides 125 mg containing omega-3 marine triglycerides 82.5 mg equivalent eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) 12.5 mg equivalent docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) 62.5 mg Iron (II) glycinate 9.25 mg equivalent iron 2.5 mg Colecalcif