l and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Immune System Health Common Colds & Flu Collagen Formation General Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits High potency dose. Buffered with mineral ascorbates making it gentle on the stomach. Added bioflavonoids thought to support the efficacy of vitamin C. Simply mix with food or drink. Reduces the severity and duration of common cold symptoms. Supports collagen formation. Supports general health and wellbeing. Contains antioxidant properties and helps reduce free radicals formed in the body. Dosage Adults Take 1 g (1 level scoop using measuring scoop enclosed) a day with a meal, or as prescribed by a health professional. Add powder to fruit juice or water. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Adults only. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Benefits Dosage Warnings High potency dose. Buffered with mineral ascorbates making it gentle on the stomach. Added bioflavonoids thought to support the efficacy of vitamin C. Simply mix with food or drink. Reduces the severity and duration of common cold symptoms. Supports collagen formation. Supports general health and wellbeing. Contains antioxidant properties and helps reduce free radicals formed in the body. Adults Take 1 g (1 level scoop using measuring scoop enclosed) a day with a meal, or as prescribed by a health professional. Add powder to fruit j