mat Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Wound Healing Cold Sores Immune System Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Relieves symptoms of facial cold sores. Supports immune system health. Supports wound healing. Lysine is an essential amino acid that cannot be synthesised by the body and must be obtained from the diet. Dosage Adults Dose for risk reduction – 2 tablets per day with meals. Dose for managements of outbrea k – 2 tablets, 2 times per day with meals, or as prescribed by a health professional. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow directions for use. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. Contains zinc, which may be dangerous when used in large amounts or for a long time. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Benefits Dosage Warnings Relieves symptoms of facial cold sores. Supports immune system health. Supports wound healing. Lysine is an essential amino acid that cannot be synthesised by the body and must be obtained from the diet. Adults Dose for risk reduction – 2 tablets per day with meals. Dose for managements of outbrea k – 2 tablets, 2 times per day with meals, or as prescribed by a health professional. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Always read the label and follow directions for use. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequ